FT  10 APR 93 / International Company News: Laidlaw hampered by bad weather
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
LAIDLAW, the international waste management group, says bad weather and the
recession dampened its second-quarter results.
Net profit was USDollars 28.1m or 10 cents a share in the three months ended
February 28, against Dollars 28.2m, or 11 cents, a year earlier. Revenues
were Dollars 469m, up 1.4 a cent. There were more shares outstanding in the
latest quarter.
First-half profit rose to Dollars 77m, or 28 cents a share, up 12 per cent
from Dollars 68.7m, or 27 cents, a year earlier. Revenues were Dollars 982m
against Dollars 984m.
ADT, the security and vehicle auction company, and Attwoods, the waste
management group, provided Dollars 11m in the latest quarter, against
Dollars 8.9m a year earlier.
