<HEADLINE>
FT  10 APR 93 / UK Company News: GPA suffers further ratings downgrade
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GPA Group, the financially-troubled Irish aircraft leasing company, has
suffered a further downgrade in ratings by the Moody's agency.
About Dollars 1.8bn of debt has been downgraded to Caa from B1, which was
already in the speculative rather than investment grade.
Moody's said the change reflected the uncertain outcome of the company's
financial restructuring negotiations with aircraft manufacturers, lenders,
and shareholders. It was concerned that efforts to restructure GPA
financially could be jeopardised if shareholders failed to come up with
Dollars 200m in new equity, or if new shareholders were not found to fill
the gap.
</TEXT>
