<HEADLINE>
FT  08 APR 93 / London Stock Exchange: Rothmans hit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE, PETER JOHN, JOEL KIBAZO and STEVE THOMPSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Worries over the prospects for tobacco groups in particular and the value of
branded goods in general spilled over into Rothmans International, the 'B'
shares dropping 27 to 615p.
Rothmans does not sell cigarettes in the US and would not be hit by the
recent announcement from Philip Morris of a price war. However, analysts
said Philip Morris's decision to drop the price of its Marlboro brand had
prompted the market to look at companies with any cigarette exposure and
also group's with highly valued brands. Rothmans markets luxury goods under
the Dunhill and Cartier labels. BAT Industries, whose shares were savaged by
the Philip Morris move last week, declined 6 to 874p.
