FT  08 APR 93 / International Company News: CBS man tipped for NBC after
rigged truck report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
NBC NEWS is expected to name CBS News producer Mr Andrew Lack as president
in an effort to restore its tarnished reputation after the rigging of a
broadcast test of a General Motors truck last year.
There has been widespread speculation about who will head the news division
since March, when the third-ranking television network announced the
resignation of the division's president, Mr Michael Gartner. Mr Lack
appeared to be the front-runner yesterday.
Mr Lack, 45, who has been at CBS News for 16 years, was named executive
producer of CBS's prime-time news magazine show, Street Stories, this year.
He also produces specials and is credited with reviving CBS's documentaries
with a string of successes, including Malcolm X: The Real Story, Remember
Pearl Harbor and Watergate: The Secret Story.
NBC, a unit of General Electric, had to apologise on air after it showed
pictures of a blazing GM truck without telling viewers that incendiary
devices had been attached to make the truck burst into flames in a
collision.
