<HEADLINE>
FT  08 APR 93 / UK Company News: Blockleys tumbles to Pounds 352,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BLOCKLEYS, the Shropshire-based brick and pavior manufacturer, suffered a
further downturn in 1992 as recession continued to take its toll on the
construction industry.
On turnover down by Pounds 1m to Pounds 9.3m, pre-tax profits were Pounds
352,000, against Pounds 1.06m.
Mr Brian Taylor, chairman and managing director, said the UK brick industry
saw both production and sales fall by some 6 per cent, while stocks of
bricks rose to a new peak of 1.54bn at the year end.
There is still no real indication of any recovery in the construction
industry, he said, and the forecast for sales of bricks in 1993 was only 2.5
per cent above the 1992 level.
Staff numbers have been cut by 45, leading to an exceptional charge of
Pounds 85,000.
A final dividend of 0.5p (1.43p) makes a total of 1p (3.38p). The dividend
is uncovered by earnings per share of 0.73p (2.48p).
