FT  08 APR 93 / UK Company News: Campaign to save Clark launched
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PEGGY HOLLINGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A CAMPAIGN against the sale of C&amp;J Clark, the family owned shoe
manufacturer, was officially launched yesterday with a letter to 300
shareholders urging them to resist the board's proposals.
Shareholders Opposed to Enforced Sale (Shoes), run by five Clark family
members, urged investors not to sell at a price reflecting 'the  .. past
rather than the future.'
The letter points to Clark's recent results, showing a fall in debt and a
net asset value of 278p per share. 'This does not include the value of the
brand,' the letter states. Berisford is believed to be offering about 205p.
Mr Charles Robertson, of Shoes, said many shareholders were upset over how
the sale proposal had been handled. 'Shareholders are disaffected because
they were not properly informed,' he said.
The letter urged those wanting to sell to resist the temptation. 'Even those
who favour a sale should recognise this is a particularly inopportune time
to sell.'
</TEXT>
