<BYLINE>
   By DANIEL GREEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
DEWHIRST Group, one of Marks and Spencer's main clothing suppliers, reported
improved margins in the year to January 15 1993 which pushed pre-tax profits
up from Pounds 4.13m to Pounds 6.46m.
Turnover was up from Pounds 130.5m to Pounds 181.6m but was swollen by the
