FT  08 APR 93 / UK Company News: Wardle Storeys downturn
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANGUS FOSTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
WARDLE Storeys, the plastics and safety equipment concern, yesterday
reported a fall in interim profits mainly because of lower interest earnings
and an accounting change.
Pre-tax profits fell from a restated Pounds 4.92m to Pounds 4.04m in the six
months to February 28.
The restatement, prompted by adopting FRS 3 led to the reclassification of a
Pounds 563,000 gain as exceptional rather than extraordinary, thereby
lifting the prior year figure.
Operating profits increased 3 per cent to Pounds 2.74m on unchanged turnover
of Pounds 38.2m.
Net cash fell slightly from Pounds 34m to Pounds 31.3m. Lower interest rates
meant net interest received fell from Pounds 1.7m to Pounds 1.31m.
Earnings fell from an adjusted 14p to 10.9p. The company said it planned to
increase this year's dividend to compensate shareholders who would otherwise
lose out because of changes to the rates of ACT introduced following the
budget. The interim dividend is lifted 25 per cent to 5p.
