FT  08 APR 93 / UK Company News: Ingham makes cash call and Pounds 4.5m
acquisition
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
INGHAM, the worsted spinner, yesterday said it was proceeding with the
acquisition of Moss Europe and raising Pounds 3.64m through a 1-for-4 rights
issue of up to 4.04m new shares at 100p.
Moss, which supplies parts for British classic sports cars, is being bought
for Pounds 4.5m, satisfied by the issue of 3.4m shares and payment of Pounds
1.5m cash. It made Pounds 544,000 pre-tax on Pounds 13.6m turnover in 1992.
Net assets were Pounds 2.66m.
In addition, Ingham has entered into certain arrangements and contracts with
the vendors, Milard - the principal shareholder - Howard Goldman and Glen
Adams, which include the sale of the enlarged group's US business to Milard
in exchange for Milard convertible loan stock.
Ingham is paying a second interim dividend of 4.5p in respect of the 15
months to end-March and declared its intention to pay total dividends of not
less than 4.7p for the year to March 31 1994.
