FT  08 APR 93 / Funding Sources: Correction
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A REPORT (Financial Times, March 17) on the winding-up of Funding Sources
International Limited (FSI) mentioned DTI warnings about Prime Bank Notes
offered by the company.
Mr Howard Curtis, former director of FSI, faces charges under the Companies
Act. He asks us to make clear that he has not been charged with any offence
regarding wrongful obtaining or retention of fees, that it is not suggested
he has been involved in any way therewith, and that he has not been
convicted of any charge in connection with FSI.
